<br>
Ahnmei blinked at her father. What was he up to now? Meet people? He didn't mention anything about meeting anybody until now. &quot;I don't have any plans, Papa.&quot; She cocked her head sideways and gave him a curious glance. &quot;Who are we meeting with?&quot; <br>
<br>
His broad grin faded just a bit, a touch of worry seeped into his eyes. His quick flash of a false smile didn't hide the fact that she saw it. &quot;We...well, it's a surprise. Just be ready to go after lunch. And look your best!&quot; He threw on his cloak and hurried out the door. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ahnmei>Ahnmei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/25/03 8:33:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=912.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.knology.net/~ahnmei/Vahicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Finis</span><hr size=1> Had Ahnmei known that she’d be presented to King Raja Kerrath, she would’ve ran away as soon as her father had left the house earlier that day! What was he thinking? Why was she even here? The butterflies in her belly where flying in tight circles so fast it almost made her sick. As they spoke quietly near the throne, she stroked the fur on her tail; a bad habit she acquired as a small child - for when she was nervous or scared. <br>
<br>
Ahnmei’s father bowed before the King before approaching his bewildered daughter, who was busy trying to make a bald spot on her tail’s tip. She gave King Raja a clumsy curtsey as her father pulled her elbow to take her away. <br>
<br>
He was leading her down a richly decorated hallway in the Palace when she stopped in her tracks. “Papa!” she hissed. “What was that all about? What’s going on?” She was almost in tears with confusion. “It’s obvious you two were discussing something about me, because you two kept looking at me. Tell me!” She stomped a defiant foot on the plush carpet. <br>
<br>
His furry eyebrows arched then fell as he let out a deep, growling sigh. “I can’t just now, puss. Have a little faith in your Papa. Please…come with me.” Ahnmei’s maw clamped shut tightly; she was obviously very disturbed, but trusted her father. He placed a graying paw on her back as he led her further down the hallway, down past the Scribe Shop, and into the Spiritist’s Quarters. <br>
<br>
“Ahh, Mr. Jin Mir’ Sher, and you must be Ahnmei. Please, come in.” Spiritist Cholsa greeted the pair with a warm smile as she welcomed them. Ahnmei wrinkled her nose at the assault of pungent incense, but remained silent as she sat down next to her father. <br>
<br>
Two older Vah Shir males introduced themselves as a Spiritist Grawleh and Rahleh. Grawleh, appearing to be the Eldest and most respected of the three, took Ahnmei by the paws, coaxing her to stand up. He walked around her in a tight circle, looking her up and down. Ahnmei’s tail automatically went into her paws again as she cast a worried look towards her father. <br>
<br>
Spiritist Grawleh stopped his encirclement to look Ahnmei in the face. “Your father has requested our aid. Do you have any idea why?” <br>
<br>
“N…no, sir.” <br>
<br>
“He says you’re unruly, that you don’t heed warnings from your dead mother and from himself about your safety. He says that you are on a personal mission, but are not properly suited to fulfill it. He says he can’t control your actions any more. Is this true?” <br>
<br>
Ahnmei glared at her father for a second, then cast her eyes to the floor. Her ears flicked with embarrassment. “Yes, sir. It’s all true, I guess, ‘cept I was doing just fine until the other day…”<br>
<br>
Grawleh cut her off, “By the King’s orders and your father’s, from this moment forward, you now belong to the Dar Khura sect. Are you aware of what that entails?” <br>
<br>
Ahnmei’s eyes grew big with curiosity. “Does that mean I have to learn silly magics, and light candles and stuff when I could be out hunting mutts?”<br>
<br>
The whole room tensed as Grawleh’s fur bristled. He bared his fangs to the young Vah Shir, getting dangerously close to her face. “Don’t you EVER say such a thing again! Do you think your mother’s spiritual presence is silly? Do you think being able to heal yourself after near death from a fight is silly? Do you think helping others is silly?” Ahnmei shook her head slowly and gulped hard. “You belong to this House. You will study the arts of the Dar Khura to the BEST of your abilities alongside the King’s son, and you will join his Pride Pack to learn some humility and responsibility. You will only be allowed to live at home with your father as long as you behave and follow the rules. This is my word, your father’s word, and most importantly, the King’s word!” <br>
<br>
The young Vah Shir sobbed quietly and nodded her head. How could her father do this to her? Did he not love her? She was thoroughly cross with him. He sensed her frustration and stood to leave after whispering an emotional “Goodbye and good luck.” <br>
<br>
It was at the time of his departure when a heavily plate-clad Vah Shir entered the Quarter. He was introduced to her as Sekayn, leader and champion of the Pride known as the Chosen of Vah. <br>
<br>
This marked the beginning of Ahnmei’s new life as a Chosen Dar Khura. <br>
